Repro:

```cs
public void M(string x)
{
    string a = "test";
    string v = a + "\n" + x + "\n" + x + "done" + a + x + x + x;
    Console.WriteLine(v);
}
```

The current codegen simply builds an array and then calls `string.Concat`. Instead we should emit code using `DefaultInterpolatedStringHandler` for this.

Fixing this can be meaningful as such patterns are very common in real-world code (despite we already have raw interpolated string, many people still choose to use `+` to build a string as they think it is simple).

